<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Elle Fanning was praised by fans on Monday night after she shared a candid makeup-free snap showing her eczema. </p>

<p>The Maleficent star, 22, took to Instagram to post three different selfies of her face with her blonde locks sweptback and no filter used.   </p>

<p>Elle captioned the pictures with: 'Eczema but make it eye shadow.'</p>

<p>Praised: Elle Fanning was praised by fans on Monday night after she shared candid makeup-free snaps showing her eczema</p>

<p>Eczema is a condition that causes the skin to become itchy, red, dry and cracked. Some people only have small patches of dry skin, but others may experience widespread inflammation.  </p>

<p>The All the Bright Places star's 4.8 million followers were quick to praise the actress for her candid photos and lauded her for showing 'real normal skin' on social media.</p>

<p>One person said: 'Thank you for not using like a dozen filters, its so nice seeing real normal skin texture on this app and it makes me feel good about myself.'</p>

<p>The Maleficent star, 22, captioned the photos with: 'Eczema but make it eye shadow.' </p>

